description.narrative: By 2021, strengthened multisectoral capacity for scaling up nutrition interventions, which contributes to Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Micronutrients, Nutrition And Emergencies, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Effective and efficient management of the Education Programme.

title.narrative: By 2021, strengthened multisectoral capacity for scaling up nutrition interventions

description.narrative: UNICEF continued to strengthen the capacity of the Government of Laos for multisectoral action. This included the development and finalization of the National Plan of Action for Nutrition 2021-25 and the commencement of an independent review of the multisectoral coordination mechanisms. The enabling environment was improved through development and initial roll out of an innovative real time monitoring tool for the monitoring of violations of the national decree on Breast Milk Substitutes, service delivery strengthened through increased number of trained staff and equitable distribution of nutrition commodities, while demand for services and practices were enhanced through a national MIYCN campaign. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2022
